Our Fire glass will not melt, degrade or emit toxic fumes. There is also no soot, ash or smoke. Calculator for Circular or Rounded Fire Pits or Fire Bowls How much fire glass will you need? To calculate the amount of fire pit glass needed to fill a circular fire pit, use the following equation: Diameter X Diameter X Depth, divided by 24 = pounds of fire glass needed. We recommend a minimum 2” of fire glass depth for most installations. For example, a 25" diameter fire pit at the recommended 2” of fire glass depth: 25 X 25 X 2, divided by 24 = 52 lbs. Calculator for Square or Rectangle Fire Pit How much fire glass will you need? To calculate the amount of fire pit glass needed to fill a square or rectangular fire pit, use the following equation: Width X Length X Depth, divided by 19 = pounds of fire glass needed. We recommend a minimum 2” of fire glass depth for most installations. For example, a 48" X 14" fire pit at the recommended 2” of fire glass depth: 48 X 14 X 2, divided by 19 = 70 lbs.    Fire glass is often used in outdoor fire pits, fire bowls and fire tables. It can be used exclusively or placed on top of a base layer of fire rock or sand.
